<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.5151 Williams Mission/24:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-17T19:00:00-04:00">July 17, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>83. For Doctor Williams. Recent developments in the exchange situation in
                            Uruguay prejudicial to American interests make it seem highly important
                            that you visit Montevideo and study the problem there. I very much hope
                            that you will find it possible to do so, even though this may mean
                            extending your trip 10 days or 2 weeks longer.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>